Shares of solar power companies tumbled in premarket trade Monday, as crude prices fell more than 22% amid a price war between Saudi Arabia and Russia. Solar stocks typically fall with crude price declines, as cheap oil makes the technology look less appealing. Electric car maker Tesla Inc. TSLA, +4.37% shares were also lower, down 14% at last check, while its Chinese rival Nio Inc. NIO, -3.71% was down 16%. Among solar stocks, Enphase Energy Inc. ENPH, +1.26% was down 14%, Vivint Solar vslr was down 12%, Canadian Solar Inc. CSIQ, -2.67% was down 11% and JinkoSolar Holding Co. Ltd. JKS, -2.04% was down 10%. First Solar Inc. FSLR, -1.45% and SolarEdge Technologies Inc. SEDG, +0.31% were down 10%, Sunrun Inc. RUN, -3.32% was down 9.6%. 